The Telegraph - Calcutta : Nation

 Gill demand

 New Delhi, May 6: The newly appointed special adviser to the Chhattisgarh government, K.P.S. Gill, has asked for 10 more battalions ? approximately 11,000 personnel ? of central paramilitary forces from the Centre to counter Naxalites.

 This is in addition to the sanction which the Centre gave the state recently to raise two reserve battalions.




